HEADWORD: Patent-hammered
<hw>Pat"ent-ham"mered</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <fld>(Stone
Cutting)</fld> <def>Having a surface dressed by cutting with a hammer
the head of which consists of broad thin chisels clamped
together.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Patently</ent>⟦br⟧
